                                <h3>What is Quality Control?</h3>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <h4>Dictionary Definition</h4>
                                        <h5><span style="font-weight: bold;">情度管理</span></h5>
                                        <p>
                                            A series of tasks that technically and statistically manages each stage of an examination process, so that the measurements of the clinical examination always maintain a constant level of <span class="hl">accuracy</span> and <span class="hl">precision.</span><br>
                                            <span class="sub_desc">
                                                ※Accuracy: Close to the true value<br>
                                                Precision: Reproducibility of the measured value
                                            </span>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <h4>Evaluation Targets</h4>
                                        <h5><span>Environmental Testing and Inspection Act</span></h5>
                                        <p>
                                            Environmental measuring equipment inspection institution, measurement agency, and pollution level inspection institution<span class="hl">Public wastewater </span>treatment facility,
                                            public sewage treatment facility, and <span class="hl">public sewage pipe management agency</span><br>
                                            <span class="sub_desc">
                                                ※ A quality control verification certificate is maintained <br>
                                                if both the proficiency test and an on-site evaluation are deemed to be satisfactory.
                                            </span>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <h4>Relevant Law</h4>
                                        <h5><span>Environmental Testing and Inspection Act</span></h5>
                                        <p>
                                            A system for verifying the capabilities of testing and inspection institutions for testing, inspections, etc., and the data that are used in the testing, inspections, etc.
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <h4>Relevant Regulations</h4>
                                        <h5><span>Regulation on the Quality Control Operations of Environmental Testing and Inspection Institutions</span></h5>
                                        <p>
                                            In order to ensure the reliability of the test and inspection results, the testing and inspection institutions shall establish and implement an internal quality control system meeting the ISO 17025 standard, and will periodically receive external verifications and evaluations.<br>
                                            <span class="sub_desc">
                                                ※ Evaluation agency: National Institute of Environmental Sciences; Evaluation cycle: Every three years
                                            </span>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <h4>Proficiency Test</h4>
                                        <h5><span>Implemented every year (National Institute of Environmental Sciences)</span></h5>
                                        <p>
                                            Evaluation method: The National Institute of Environmental Sciences sends unmarked samples every year and they are judge by a Z-score. In the case of a 1st or 2nd unsuitable ruling, the laboratory will be closed for the year.<br>
                                            <span class="sub_desc">
                                                ※For management agencies, only the head office is subject to the evaluation. (Laboratories under their management are subject to a self-evaluation on their proficiency.)
                                            </span>
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <h4>On-Site Evaluations</h4>
                                        <h5><span>Implemented every three years (National Institute of Environmental Sciences)</span></h5>
                                        <p>
                                            Evaluation method: The institution subject to an on-site evaluation is announced every year. <br>
                                            Visiting and inspecting the representative laboratory (inspecting all the laboratory documents)
                                        </p>
                                    </li>
